    "Task 5 — Insights & Summary\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7889699f-0f49-4b9d-b17f-dd359d116c89",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "After analyzing the dataset, I found that the most important factors affecting house prices were the size of the house (area), the number of bathrooms, parking availability, and whether the house was located in a preferred area. The Random Forest model performed better than the Linear Regression model and was able to predict house prices with good accuracy. This means the model's predictions were generally close to the actual house prices. One thing that surprised me was how much features like parking spaces and air conditioning influenced the price, sometimes more than I expected. Based on these findings, I would recommend that real estate businesses focus on properties with larger living areas, good amenities, and desirable locations, as these features tend to increase property value the most."
   ]
